text:
Hey Gura, something I wanna mention about how you feel bad sometimes when you're not at your best for streams. If I'm being honest, one of the reasons I enjoy your streams so much is that I don't feel like I, or you, or anyone else has to show up at their best. Even when we're not happy, or energetic, or even when we just feel like complete messes who can't do anything right...in Gura streams, we're always allowed to smile and laugh and feel comfortable. 

I can't say NO ONE is judgemental, cause obviously there's a lot of people who watch, but most of the Shrimps, and Chumbuddies, and you yourself most of all, are kind to each other. Even when we drop pizza in a bathtub, or are sometimes not the best at math, or feel like we can't do things right, it doesn't mean we can't hang out and feel better for a little while. 

And literally none of that happens without you, Gura. Not because you're always smiling, or you're always funny, or you're always a pro gamer, but because you're NOT always those things. Because you don't try to pretend everything's fine, and you tell us if things are kinda bad, and you're open about the parts of you that aren't perfect, and you laugh at them and any other little things you can find worth laughing at...and you make a place where people can feel like it's okay for them to do those things, too. 

My point is, Little Shark, you deserve to have bad days and tired days as much as--maybe even MORE than--any one of us. So you don't have to feel bad when those days happen, even if those days are every day...cause Gura streams are a place for everyone to feel at home, no matter what kind of weird or different you have to be to get through life, and that will ALWAYS include you. 

(All of that said, Gura, please-PLEASE- don't feel like you have to work three times as hard to keep that up or make it better. This is all what you've already accomplished being exactly what you are, and it's far more than enough as it is. We know you've worked really hard for it, and we know you'll work your tail off for it in the future; you don't have to make yourself do more to live up to any expectations. Please take care of yourself, please take breaks--please stay with us to enjoy this wonderful home you've created.)

text: I kinda feel like rewind states aren't that big of a deal. I mean using it for a boss just means you don't have to back track to the boss. Its not everything else that is the issue. Its just the boss so why do all the other stuff again lol? So you may lose a bit more HP or w/e, but if you make it to the boss and die just rewind and start from there. Saves time, but I mean you still gotta beat it on your own merit. Also, creating a save state is like the same thing as a rewind except instead of rewinding you just start from there to not waste time backtracking. I wouldn't bat an eye, but some ppl are really hung up about the save states and rewind as "cheating"

(Pain + (0))-(1/Pain)=Peko
((Pain^2)/Pain)-(1/Pain)=Peko
((Pain^2)-1)/Pain=Peko.
Pain Peko = (Pain^2)-1
which makes more sense IMO.
